article.headline: E. Washington 17, N. Colorado 7
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. (AP) -- A.J. Jimerson rushed for 100 yards and the Eastern Washington defense forced three key turnovers in a 17-7 victory over Northern Colorado on Saturday. Matt Nichols threw for one touchdown and Dale Morris rushed for another for the Eagles (6-3 overall, 4-2 Big Sky). David Woods' 102 yards rushing led the Bears (1-9, 1-5), who were seeking their first back-to-back wins in almost four years. With EWU trailing 7-3 midway through the third quarter, Shane Eller took Nichols' short pass and ran 29 yards for the go-ahead score. UNC took the ensuing kickoff to Eastern's 25, but Dominic Breazeale's pass was intercepted by Ryan Kelley at the 2-yard line. Eastern's next possession resulted in a punt, but the Eagles' Nicholas Ramos recovered a fumble on the return at the UNC 31. Nichols then hit Aaron Boyce for 29 yards, setting up Morris' short plunge that put the Eagles up 17-7. Nichols finished with 172 yards on 14-of-23 passing. Boyce had five catches for 87 yards. Breazeale completed 18-of-26 for 146 yards for the Bears, who opened a 7-0 lead on Woods' 7-yard TD run. UNC had a chance to increase the lead early in the second quarter, but fumbled a shovel pass at Eastern's 1-yard line that was recovered by the Eagles' Makai Borden. Northern Colorado had lost 16 straight games before knocking off Montana State last week.
